<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-217-330 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 393 375</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Feb 25 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>IBM Japan opens OS architecture to American software makers.andO;(operating system DOS/V)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Miyazawa, Masayuki.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   IBM Japan Ltd. (Products).andO;Product:   MS-DOS 5.0 (Operating system) (Design and construction).andO;Topic:     JapanOperating SystemsSoftware Design.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>IBM JAPAN OPENS OS ARCHITECTURE TO AMERICAN SOFTWARE MAKERS 02/25/91 TOKYO,JAPAN, 1991 FEB 25 (NB) -- IBM Japan will provide technical information onits latest personal computers and its operating system DOS/V to majorsoftware makers in the U.S., reports the Nippon Kogyo daily newspaper.andP;  Thefirm wants the American software makers to modify their software for theJapanese version of the IBM PC.andM;This is part of IBM Japan's latest operation called the &quot;Open ArchitectureDeveloper's Group&quot; scheme.andP;  According to IBM Japan's Vice President NobuoMitsui, the firm will provide technical information on both hardware andsoftware to Japanese personal computer makers, and encourage them tomanufacture their own Japanese IBM PC-compatible personal computers.andM;IBM Japan already held the first introductory gathering of about 180 Japanesesoftware makers in Tokyo this past January.andM;IBM Japan's Vice President Nobuo Mitsui will fly to the U.S.andP;  this March andwill hold a similar meeting.andP;  It is said 50 to 60 software makers includingmost of the major US software firms, will participate in the meeting.andM;(Masayuki Miyazawa/19910225/Press Contact: IBM Japan,  andplus;81-3-3586-1111)</TEXT></DOC>